the new york sun was a politically conservative weekday daily newspaper published in new york city from 2002 to 2008. when it debuted on april 16, 2002, adopting the name, motto, and masthead of an otherwise unrelated earlier new york paper, the sun (1833â€“1950), it became the first general-interest broadsheet newspaper to be started in new york city in several decades. since 2009 the sun has operated as an online-only publisher of political and economic opinion pieces, as well as occasional arts content.